<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF326A8DFD22910A1FF1B3B7" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF326A8DFD22910A1FF1B3B7" blockId="201.[734,1329,1638,2064]" lastBlockId="201.[119,1330,2069,3093]" pageId="201" pageNumber="963">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF326A8DFC6C91081DE5BC40" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[912,997,1873,1906]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF326A8DFBE891091AA6BC43" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1044,1190,1872,1905]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">montivagus</taxonomicName>
species group. See M. Jederatus and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF326A8DFB99912A1B29BCAA" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1125,1321,1906,1945]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">M. montivagus</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF326A8DFD2391FD1DEBBCF3" box="[735,1003,1956,1985]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="indochinensis">Myotis indochinensis</taxonomicName>
appears to be sister to M. federatus (labeled as M. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF326A8DFB9C91911B22BCDB" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1120,1314,1992,2025]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">cf. montivagus</taxonomicName>
) in a clade including 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF326A8DFBDC91B61AEAB322" authorityName="Maeda &amp; Matsumura" authorityYear="1998" box="[1056,1258,2031,2064]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yanbarensis">M. yanbarensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF326A8DFF869E4C1F1DB305" box="[122,285,2069,2103]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="secundus">M. secundus</taxonomicName>
based on limited genetic data. Populations now attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF326A8DFB759E4E1EB7B36C" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="indochinensis">M. indochinensis</taxonomicName>
were previously considered to represent 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF326A8DFD079E671DBEB36C" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[763,958,2109,2143]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">M. montivagus</taxonomicName>
, including those in southwestern 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF326A8DFF139E3C1F46B3B4" box="[239,326,2149,2182]" name="China" pageId="201" pageNumber="963">China</collectingCountry>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
